time required: 45 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Core, seed, and dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Peel, halve, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}(thinly sliced). Wrap @Garlic{2%cloves} in #foil{}, sealing to make a pouch, and roast in oven until very soft, about ~{20%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{} in a large pan over medium heat. Add onion and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Stir in tomato, @Sugar{1%tsp}, and @Balsamic Vinegar{1%TBSP} (we'll be using the rest later). Cook until everything is soft and jammy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove mixture from pan and set aside.

Divide @Ground Beef{10%ounce} in half and flatten each piece into a wide, roughly ½-inch-thick circle. Place half the @Cheddar Cheese{½%cup} in the center of each circle. Fold edges of meat around cheese, shaping and sealing to create a cheese-stuffed patty. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Carefully wipe out pan used for onions with a #paper towel{}. Add a drizzle of oil and heat over medium-high heat. Place burgers in pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Don't worry if some of the cheese leaks out. It'll still be delicious!

While burgers cook, halve @Brioche Buns{2} and place on a #baking sheet{}. Toast in oven until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once garlic is done roasting, mash with a #fork{} until smooth. In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{½%TBSP}, remaining @Balsamic Vinegar{1%TBSP}, a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{}, and as much garlic as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread buns with @Ketchup{2%tbsp} and @Mayonnaise{1%TBSP}. Divide burgers between buns and top with onion jam and a small handful of @Arugula{1%ounce}. Toss remaining arugula with dressing and serve on the side.